We are in the process of cleaning up the wound, but we need a Montreal-only investigation unit and supervision to prevent a return of questionable practices.
How to clean.
I do it regularly.
Jacques Duchesneau, for his part, notes that "officials have stolen several hundred million dollars", but is particularly concerned about the role of "the officials who are involved in the tactics" if they were not involved in the fraud!
Based on a 70% share of black money in financing Quebec's election campaigns, he jokes: "I was told that this was just a faint reflection of reality".
The Quebec government proposes to limit party donations to $100, which it says would not change the situation: "Until campaign spending is strictly limited, black money will be in politics".
He recommends a complete overhaul of the system for public procurement and party financing: "We cannot go any lower; by courageously going to the bottom of things, we can rebuild the House on a more solid basis with more controls and legislation".
If this story damages the international image of Quebec and Montreal, Mr Duchesneau urges those who laugh at it to look in their own backyard...
