Ten hours later, the newborns' instincts were completely numb.
The chicks didn't respond to light or sound.
Four days later, they just died.
"Twice we hatched chicks and then stopped the whole thing because it's just impossible to work with them there", says Vladimir Sychev of the failed experiment with the chicks in space.
The last animal-cage was launched into orbit 16 years ago.
The experiments will continue in spring 2013.
