Hidden beneath highway crossings, the place is in many ways a suburb of Mexico City itself.
And the problems in the community are of a decisively urban nature.
The military was called in earlier this year to fight the drug gangs operating in the neighborhoods, and violence against women is a particularly acute problem.
In a patch of marshland near a large dump, the bodies of dozens of murdered women have been left behind in the last two years alone.
