He adds: "Self-control is transferred from one situation to another".
The child not only learns to converse but also gains self-control in other areas.
I don't think we should celebrate boredom.
We should not be too critical of them either.
Instead, our goal should be to feel comfortable even outside of the constant stream of activity and technology.
Professor Eastwood agrees with you.
"It sounds like we should be bored more often, but boredom is the tormenting, unrelenting desire to do something meaningful", he says.
